  "body": "<!--\r\nNeed help?\r\nRefer to our contributing guidelines for additional information about making a good issue:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/.github/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug**\r\nOpening this issue for posterity and so that I have something to point at from the Community Hub. We currently have a discrepancy in the way we price certain opcodes because of the way that we implemented the \"minimal\" version of EIP-2929. [We added an EIP block in Geth that enabled some of the features of EIP-2929](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/blob/b9ee2d7f01cc82c5b696252ad23b6f4b6098574d/l2geth/core/vm/eips.go#L94-L126) but did not properly implement the entirety of the access list functionality. As a result, we are charging the \"cold\" storage cost for every state access instead of charging the \"warm\" cost after a given piece of state has been touched. This creates a discrepancy that results in some contracts having issues on OE that work perfectly well on the Ethereum mainnet.\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nWe are currently planning to fix this issue with a hard fork that will bring all gas costs back in line with Ethereum mainnet. In the meantime, if you are having an issue please hop in the Optimism [discord](https://discord.optimism.io) and we can try to help you figure out a temporary workaround.\r\n",
